			<h1 align="center">Vector Based Model</h1>
			<hr>			
			
			<p>
			In its basic form, each document is represented by a vector:<br>
			– A query is also represented by a vector.<br><br>
			The coordinates of the vector are words:<br>
			– Each element of the vector represents the frequency of the word in the document or the query.	
			</p>

			<p align="center">
			<i>Each document is represented by:<br>
			<img border="0" src="images/vbm-01.GIF" width="242" height="196"><br>
			where each element in the vector represents the frequency of the word</i>
			</p>
			
			<p align="center"><i>Given a collection of document, we can represent a set of documents as a term-document matrix:			
			<img border="0" src="images/vbm-02.GIF" width="647" height="221"></i>
			</p>
			
			<p align="center"><i>A query can be represented as the following vector:<br>
			<img border="0" src="images/vbm-03.GIF" ></i>				
			</p>
			
			<p align="center"><i>To determine relevance of a document given query, we map the query and document vector to a multidimensional space and calculate how close the vector q is compare to vector d.<br>
			<img border="0" src="images/vbm-04.GIF" width="282" height="257"><br>
			Similarity can be computed using the following formula:<br>
